COA is categorized as a novel swarm-based meta-heuristic algorithm, introduced by Iraj Naruei and Farshid Keynia [52]. Its behavior for food seeking can be described by the following four phases: random motion; chain motion; improving coot position by tracing the leaders; and leader motion toward optimal zone including the food. The algorithm is started by selecting an initial population randomly, and this population is frequently estimated by the objective function until the optimal value is obtained. The randomly generated population can be evaluated as:11cootpositioni=Rand1,dim×UB-LB+LB\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
